Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (markedly elevated creatinine), proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and low blood glucose and HbA1c, suggesting possible acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired glucose handling. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying renal or hepatic pathology. Immediate clinical evaluation and nephrology referral are recommended.
